Step 2: Create Project & Install Python Libraries (Offline)
📋 Instructions
Goal: To create your ai_assistant project folder, set up an isolated Python virtual environment (venv), and install flask, GitPython, and llama-cpp-python from your USB drive.

Open a Terminal. (You can close the one from Step 1).

Navigate to your Home Directory: This is a good, standard place to create new projects.

Create the Project Folder: Make the ai_assistant directory.

Navigate Into Your New Folder.

Create the Virtual Environment: Use the python3 -m venv command to create a private Python environment named venv. This keeps your project's libraries separate from the system.

Activate the Virtual Environment: You must "source" the activate script. This is crucial. Your terminal prompt will change to show (venv) at the beginning. This must be active for the next command to work.

Install Python Libraries: Now, run the pip install command. This is the most important command.

--no-index: Tells pip "DO NOT connect to the internet."

--find-links=...: Tells pip "Look in this folder on my USB drive for the files." (You must use the correct path to your USB).

This command will take a few minutes. The llama-cpp-python library will use the C++ tools you installed in Step 1 to compile itself. This is normal.

💻 Commands
(Run these in your terminal)

Bash

# 1. Go to your home directory
cd ~

# 2. Create the project folder
mkdir ai_assistant

# 3. Enter the new folder
cd ai_assistant

# 4. Create the virtual environment
python3 -m venv venv

# 5. Activate the virtual environment
source venv/bin/activate

# 6. Install all Python libraries from your USB
#    (!!! Replace '/media/your_username/MY_USB' with your actual USB path)
pip install --no-index --find-links=/media/your_username/MY_USB/python_wheels flask GitPython llama-cpp-python
After this completes, your venv folder will contain all the necessary Python libraries.
